{"article_id":"PNtoe8pyGaAnRMhZ","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Forget the House","depth":3},{"id":1,"text":"GOP 's troubles passing a health care bill .","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"The party 's bigger problem looms in the Senate .","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"Mitch McConnell is being tasked with fixing what GOP senators and House members say","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"is a flawed Obamacare repeal proposal","depth":10},{"id":5,"text":"- one with little to no chance","depth":11},{"id":6,"text":"of passing in that chamber in its current form -","depth":11},{"id":7,"text":"in a week ' s time .","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"The Senate leader and his deputies are nevertheless barreling ahead","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"- assuming","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"a health care bill clears the House Thursday in what ' s expected to be a razor-thin vote .","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"Senate leaders say","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"they have a plan","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"to jam through legislation on a party-line vote next week","depth":11},{"id":14,"text":"before opposition has time","depth":12},{"id":15,"text":"to bubble up .","depth":12},{"id":16,"text":"And they 're sticking to it ,","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"regardless of the scant level of support right now for the proposal among Senate Republicans .","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"As currently constructed ,","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"conservative and moderate opposition would tank the bill in the Senate ,","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"where the GOP can afford to lose only two votes .","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"A handful of skeptical House members are voting for Speaker Paul Ryan ' s plan on the assumption","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"it will be improved in the Senate","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"and they ' ll get to make a decision","depth":12},{"id":24,"text":"when it comes back to the House .","depth":12},{"id":25,"text":"And some Republicans believe","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"they 're already losing political momentum with the health care debate","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"and want to pull the plug .","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"\" Maybe the best outcome is for this to fail in the House","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"so we can move on to tax reform .","depth":12},{"id":30,"text":"Which is what we should have done anyway , \"","depth":12},{"id":31,"text":"said one Republican senator ,","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"granted anonymity","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"to make a frank assessment of the party ' s political predicament .","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"Sen. Rand Paul of Kentucky , perhaps the most outspoken conservative critic of the House bill , had a similar view","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"- albeit for a different reason .","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"He wants full repeal of Obamacare ,","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"which in his view is impossible under the framework","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"constructed by Ryan .","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"\" I don ' t think","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"the Ryan bill will get out of the House .","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"There are enough conservatives","depth":12},{"id":42,"text":"to stop it , \"","depth":12},{"id":43,"text":"he said .","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"\" We ' ll start negotiating","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"when they stop it . \"","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"Senate Republicans are unlikely to hold any committee hearings ,","depth":5},{"id":47,"text":"and many of them haven ' t even read what the House is about to pass .","depth":5},{"id":48,"text":"It ' s unclear ,","depth":6},{"id":49,"text":"to put it mildly ,","depth":6},{"id":50,"text":"how proponents can placate enough moderates or conservatives","depth":6},{"id":51,"text":"to get the bill across the finish line .","depth":6},{"id":52,"text":"But GOP leaders are showing no signs","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"of applying the brakes .","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"\" We ' re not slowing down , \"","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"McConnell said on Tuesday .","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"\" We will reach a conclusion on health care next week . \"","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"While they aren ' t yet guaranteeing victory ,","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"McConnell and his deputies are moving swiftly","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"to avoid heading into a two-week April recess with the Obamacare repeal unresolved .","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"Letting the bill twist in the wind over that long break is viewed as a potential disaster","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"as opposition brews back home","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"and GOP lawmakers face antagonistic crowds at their town halls .","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"Instead , the Senate GOP asserts","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"that by the first week in April there ' s a good chance","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"the Senate will have repealed and replaced Obamacare","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"and made good on a key campaign promise from the past six years .","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"\" The question is can we as Republicans get the health care bill out of the House and through the Senate ?","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"And I ' m optimistic , \"","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"said Senate Majority Whip John Cornyn","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"( R-Texas ) .","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"He and McConnell have not started whipping their caucus yet ,","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"but right now it ' s ugly .","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"Paul and Sens . Mike Lee of Utah and Tom Cotton of Arkansas are \" no \" votes .","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"Two moderates , Sens . Susan Collins of Maine and Lisa Murkowski of Alaska , have panned recent versions of the House proposal .","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"That ' s not to mention dozens of publicly undecided members ,","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"raising concerns about everything from coverage losses to premiums increases in the short term .","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"The House tweaked some of those provisions just this week","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"to get their members on board .","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"And now some on-the-fence House Republicans say","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"they will vote in favor","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"so as not to derail the entire process .","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"\" This isn ' t the last vote","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"unless you kill it , \"","depth":12},{"id":84,"text":"said Rep. Tom Cole of Oklahoma , .","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"\" It ' s going to the United States Senate .","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"It will change . \"","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"It might take a visit from President Donald Trump to get things moving in the right direction in the Senate .","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"He 's managed to flip more than a dozen House Republicans to support the legislation ,","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"which is still short of the votes","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"it needs to pass in that chamber .","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"\" He ' s been very , very engaged .","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"And obviously it ' s a priority .","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"He ' s all in , \"","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"said Mississippi Sen. Roger Wicker , a close McConnell ally .","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"While the House can lose only 22 votes on Thursday ,","depth":7},{"id":96,"text":"Senate Republicans have even less relative margin for error .","depth":7},{"id":97,"text":"Georgia Sen. Johnny Isakson , a reliable supporter of McConnell ' s legislative priorities , is out indefinitely after two back surgeries .","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"His office says","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"he is trying to come back to the Senate as quickly","depth":12},{"id":100,"text":"as possible","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"but it ' s not clear whether he will return in time for the Obamacare debate .","depth":11},{"id":102,"text":"Without Isakson ,","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"it may be impossible to pass a bill before the recess .","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"\" We ' ve got all these big votes coming up .","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"He ' ll be here","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"as quick","depth":12},{"id":107,"text":"as he can , \"","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"said Sen. David Perdue of Georgia .","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"\" I just know Johnny well enough","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"to know","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"he ' ll be here","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"before his doctors even say","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"it ' s OK.","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"He ' ll be back here","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"when we need him . \"","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"Even with a full voting contingent , it ' s hard to overstate the amount of work","depth":8},{"id":117,"text":"that McConnell is taking on in a short time .","depth":8},{"id":118,"text":"Placating conservatives and moderates simultaneously is enormously difficult .","depth":7},{"id":119,"text":"To win Paul and Lee ' s vote ,","depth":8},{"id":120,"text":"McConnell must pursue a more fulsome repeal ,","depth":8},{"id":121,"text":"but","depth":8},{"id":122,"text":"to win over Collins and Murkowski ,","depth":9},{"id":123,"text":"he must move parts of the bill to the center .","depth":9},{"id":124,"text":"Sign up here for Huddle","depth":4},{"id":125,"text":"A daily play-by-play of congressional news in your inbox .","depth":4},{"id":126,"text":"Email Sign Up","depth":5},{"id":127,"text":"By signing up","depth":7},{"id":128,"text":"you agree to receive email newsletters or alerts from .","depth":7},{"id":129,"text":"You can unsubscribe at any time .","depth":6},{"id":130,"text":"This site is protected by reCAPTCHA","depth":5},{"id":131,"text":"and the Google Privacy Policy and Terms of Service apply .","depth":5},{"id":132,"text":"\" Alaska is a high-cost state , low population and no competition with an aging population ...","depth":6},{"id":133,"text":"all of the demographic factors don ' t play well with the approach","depth":7},{"id":134,"text":"the House is taken , \"","depth":7},{"id":135,"text":"Murkowski said in an interview .","depth":5},{"id":136,"text":"\" You ' re going to have to show me","depth":5},{"id":137,"text":"that the level of support for an Alaskan in a high-cost state is going to be fair . \"","depth":5},{"id":138,"text":"Another factor :","depth":6},{"id":139,"text":"Key provisions of the bill could be stricken in the Senate","depth":8},{"id":140,"text":"because Democrats plan to argue","depth":10},{"id":141,"text":"that language","depth":12},{"id":142,"text":"restricting tax credits from being used for abortions and Medicaid work requirements","depth":12},{"id":143,"text":"are not allowed under Senate rules .","depth":11},{"id":144,"text":"That could prompt more concern from conservatives .","depth":9},{"id":145,"text":"\" We ' ve looked at this backwards and forwards ,","depth":9},{"id":146,"text":"and believe","depth":10},{"id":147,"text":"there is almost no chance","depth":11},{"id":148,"text":"these provisions would survive , \"","depth":11},{"id":149,"text":"said a senior Democratic aide .","depth":8},{"id":150,"text":"Still , things only get tougher for the GOP","depth":8},{"id":151,"text":"the longer the bill hangs out there .","depth":8},{"id":152,"text":"So McConnell is vowing to finish the bill next week ,","depth":8},{"id":153,"text":"reckoning","depth":9},{"id":154,"text":"that such a deadline will drive consensus .","depth":9},{"id":155,"text":"\" I would prefer more time , \"","depth":8},{"id":156,"text":"said Louisiana Sen. Bill Cassidy ,","depth":9},{"id":157,"text":"who is concerned about projections","depth":10},{"id":158,"text":"showing","depth":11},{"id":159,"text":"24 million more people will be uninsured under Ryan ' s proposal than under current law .","depth":11},{"id":160,"text":"\" I don ' t think","depth":9},{"id":161,"text":"it ' s going to be easy , \"","depth":9},{"id":162,"text":"said Senate Finance Committee Chairman Orrin Hatch","depth":9},{"id":163,"text":"( R-Utah ) .","depth":9},{"id":164,"text":"Though McConnell guarantees","depth":7},{"id":165,"text":"that Neil Gorsuch will be confirmed to the Supreme Court before the April recess ,","depth":7},{"id":166,"text":"he ' s a bit more circumspect","depth":7},{"id":167,"text":"when it comes to repealing Obamacare .","depth":7},{"id":168,"text":"\" We ' ll either pass something","depth":7},{"id":169,"text":"that will achieve a goal","depth":9},{"id":170,"text":"that we ' ve been working on , ''","depth":9},{"id":171,"text":"he said .","depth":8},{"id":172,"text":"`` Or not . \"","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":345,"left":296,"right":344,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":296,"left":218,"right":295,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":218,"left":0,"right":217,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":217,"left":1,"right":216,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":216,"left":181,"right":215,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":181,"left":178,"right":180,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":178,"left":2,"right":177,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":177,"left":3,"right":176,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":176,"left":175,"right":7,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":175,"left":4,"right":174,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":174,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":180,"left":8,"right":179,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":179,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":215,"left":203,"right":214,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":203,"left":187,"right":202,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":187,"left":185,"right":186,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":185,"left":11,"right":184,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":184,"left":12,"right":183,"rel